Reasoning: The paper deals with lower bounds and pseudorandom generators in a distributed message passing model, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The specific model studied is the Broadcast Congested Clique model, which is a variant of the Congested Clique model, falling under the category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of the pseudorandom generator. Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) is also relevant due to the use of pseudorandom generators. Finally, the paper involves constructing and analyzing graph families, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
